<P>
 SEX AND DEATH: Some courthouse watchers bet against it because, as one lawyer 
argued, people are reluctant to kill mother figures. But the Van Nuys jury 
surprised them, recommending the death penalty for a woman.That puts Mary Ellen 
Samuels in line to join a very small club. To date, only four of 503 people 
executed by California were women (A20). Although there are 377 men on Death 
Row in San Quentin now, there are only four women. . . . One of the others was 
sent there from the Van Nuys courthouse too. 
