 HEAT TOLERANT: Hot-weather gardening means extra watering. But more critical 
is choosing plants that can take the heat, says Gary Krause, Pierce College 
landscape professor. "If people want things that are lusher . . .they should 
reduce the size of these plantings." Valley Life! Page 18 
</P>
