 FAIR PRIORITIES: At last year's San Fernando Valley Fair, Kimberly Keeble's 
prize turkey won $950. At this rate, her parents figure each of their four 
children -- who enter animals every year -- could save enough money for 
college. Kimberly figures otherwise. "I want a car when I can drive," says the 
10-year-old Sun Valley girl. . . . The four-day fair opened Thursday in Burbank 
(B1). 
