Hurtado, 21, outside a Panorama City convenience store at Van Nuys Boulevard 
and Plummer Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Hurtado had returned to her car where her daughter, sister-in-law and niece 
were waiting. Gunfire erupted and a stray bullet struck Hurtado in the chest. 
She died at a hospital. Police believe that Hammond was shooting at a group of 
men who were behind Hurtado's car in a dispute over who could sell drugs on 
that corner. 
