 Robinson, formerly of Las Vegas, faces 25 years to life in prison when Judge 
Michael Harwin sentences him Aug. 29. 
</P>
<P>
 Robinson's trial featured gruesome testimony about law student Worrell's fatal 
injuries, and appearances by Robinson's two co-defendants. One implicated him; 
the other tried to clear him. 
</P>
<P>
 Robinson denied any role in the attack during his own testimony and claimed 
that he was framed. 
