<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; ACCUSED 
RAPIST INDICTED IN KIDNAPING OF WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A federal grand jury Thursday indicted an accused rapist for allegedly 
kidnaping a Castaic real estate broker and taking her to Arizona, where she was 
found tied up in a motel room.  
</P>
<P>
 Timothy Daniel Shue, 38, faces life in prison if convicted of abducting Paula 
Doreen Harrington, 26.She was lured from her office June 29 after Shue asked 
her to show him several properties.  
