<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / NORTHWEST: BUENA PARK; MAN INJURED AFTER DRIVING INTO 
PIZZERIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAIME ABDO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 33-year-old man drove his car into a pizza restaurant Thursday, injuring 
himself and one of the owners. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the driver hit a curb, a street sign and lost control of the car 
before ramming into the restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 Joseph Robert Chavez of Santa Ana, who was arrested on suspicion of felony 
drunken driving, was airlifted to UCI Medical Center in Orange after being 
found unconscious, Police Sgt. Bob Chaney said. Chaney said it was not 
immediately known what evidence officers had to arrest the suspect. 
</P>
<P>
 Chavez, who is in serious condition, was driving south on Indiana Avenue just 
before 2:30 p.m. when his car swerved across the street, hit the curb and then 
the street sign. Chaney said the man then lost control of his car, which 
crashed into the front of Frank's Italian Food, 8242 Commonwealth Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Chavez's car wound up four feet inside the building. One of the owners was hit 
by flying debris, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hye Cha Kuark, 36, had minor cuts on her knee and ankle and was taken to 
Martin Luther Hospital in Anaheim for treatment and released, Chaney said. 
JAIME ABDO 
</P>
