SAN CLEMENTE MAN PLEADS GUILTY TO LEWD ACTS WITH GIRL, 14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 30-year-old San Clemente man who had been working as a high school coach and 
college instructor pleaded guilty Thursday to a count of committing lewd acts 
with a 14-year-old girl. 
</P>
<P>
 As part of the plea agreement in South Municipal Court, Andrew Earl Malone was 
sentenced to three years' probation, 57 days on work furlough and 90 days of 
jail through a home electronic surveillance program, according to his lawyer, 
Paul Wallin. 
</P>
<P>
 Malone, who had no prior criminal record, contended that the victim initially 
told him she was 18 years old, then 17, and that the brief relationship did not 
involve intercourse, Wallin said. 
</P>
<P>
 Since his arrest in March, Malone has lost his job as a walk-on boys' 
basketball and baseball coach at San Clemente High School and as a part-time 
geology instructor at Saddleback College. "This is really a tremendous 
nightmare" for him, Wallin said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, who does not attend San Clemente High School, told police 
investigators that she had sexual intercourse with Malone at his home in 
February, according to court records. 
</P>
