<HEADLINE>
<P>
STUDENT SUES DEPUTY DIST. ATTY. WHO ALLEGEDLY DROVE INTO HIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Saddleback College student has filed a lawsuit against an Orange County 
deputy district attorney, alleging that she intentionally struck him with her 
van as he walked through a crowded campus parking lot last summer. 
</P>
<P>
 John Stevens, 22, who said his knee was injured in the July 20, 1993, 
incident, is seeking unspecified damages from Kelly MacEachern and her husband, 
Neil. 
</P>
<P>
 Donald E. Connors, who is representing Stevens, said Thursday that his client 
is making a good recovery and that he is optimistic the suit will be settled 
out of court. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's playing basketball again -- that was his big concern," Connors said. 
</P>
<P>
