<P>
CHURCH TO MARK 50TH ANNIVERSARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's oldest Roman Catholic church will celebrate its 50th anniversary 
Saturday with a Mass by Cardinal Roger Mahony. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mass will be attended by former priests who led services at Our Lady of 
Perpetual Help Church in Newhall more than 30 years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The hourlong service will be at 5:30 p.m. at the church, 23233 Lyons Ave., 
said Father Patrick Power, the church priest. A reception will follow in the 
parish hall. 
</P>
<P>
 Eight priests who taught at the church as far back as 1961 will attend, he 
said. In addition, high-ranking members of the Catholic fraternal organization, 
the Knights of Columbus, will serve as ushers and lecturers during the Mass. 
</P>
<P>
 A 50-page yearbook highlighting the parish's 50 years in the Santa Clarita 
Valley will be sold for $6 following services Saturday and Sunday. 
