EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; SUSPECTED CAR THIEF ARRESTED AFTER 
CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley police arrested a Los Angeles man Thursday on suspicion of 
stealing a car and evading arrest after he led officers on a brief high-speed 
chase that started on the Simi Valley Freeway and ended in the San Fernando 
Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Ruben Yepez, 20, was arrested about 6 a.m. after he lost control of the 1988 
Chevy Camaro and rolled onto the shoulder of the Simi Valley Freeway near 
Reseda Boulevard, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Yepez had stolen the vehicle about a half-hour earlier from a Simi Valley 
resident, police said. The name of the resident was not available Thursday. A 
Simi Valley police officer spotted Yepez in the vehicle driving southbound on 
the Simi Valley Freeway near Kuehner Drive, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The officer followed Yepez until he was joined by a second police cruiser on 
the freeway near Tampa Avenue in the San Fernando Valley. When the pair 
attempted to pull Yepez over, he sped off, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 After pursuing him at high speeds for about a mile, Yepez lost control of the 
vehicle, authorities said. He was taken into custody without injury, 
authorities said. KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
