<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Magazine Faults Airline Maintenance: Millions of passengers have departed 
American airports in planes unfit to leave the ground, Conde Nast Traveler said 
in a report to be published in the magazine's August issue. Leaky hydraulic 
pumps, tangled oxygen masks and other violations have not been enough to stop 
the planes from taking off, but they have cost U.S. airlines millions of 
dollars in fines in the past eight years, the magazine said. 
</P>
