<TEXT>
<P>
 Litton Gets Contract for More Destroyers: Litton Industries Inc. said it was 
given an $836.7-million contract from the Navy to build three additional Aegis 
class destroyers at Litton's Ingalls shipyard in Pascagoula, Miss. The award is 
part of the Navy's recently announced plan to temporarily abandon competitive 
bids and divide construction awards for destroyers between Beverly Hills-based 
Litton and Bath Iron Works Corp. in order to maintain an industrial base for 
ships. The Navy has already ordered 32 of the destroyers, including 14 from 
Ingalls. 
