<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coke Names New President: M. Douglas Ivester was also named chief operating 
officer and director of the world's largest soft drink company, putting him in 
line to succeed Chairman and Chief Executive Roberto Goizueta.Ivester, who was 
principal operating officer for Coca-Cola Co.'s North America operations, 
succeeds Donald Keough, who retired in April, 1993. Ivester also held the title 
of executive vice president. Coke also said Jack Stahl, senior vice president 
and chief financial officer, has been appointed president of Coca-Cola USA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
