<P>
 Navy Hires D.C. Law Firm in A-12 Dispute: The service has awarded a 
$7.8-million contract to Arnold & Porter, a large Washington law firm, for 
legal work in the A-12 attack-jet lawsuit filed against the government by 
McDonnell Douglas and General Dynamics.The contract indicates that the Navy is 
getting ready to capitulate in the legal fight but must first obtain a second 
opinion before going to Congress with a settlement, which could be as much as 
$3.5 billion. Attorneys at the firm did not return calls. By some estimates, 
the defense companies and the government are collectively spending $80 million 
annually litigating the charge that the Navy improperly canceled the firms' 
A-12 contract. 
