</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Interactive: Columbia Pictures plans to intensify its efforts to promote its 
films on-line. Working with Los Angeles-based Hollywood Online Inc., the studio 
will create video clips, photo and text materials based on its movies, which 
subscribers to on-line services can look at and download to their personal 
computers. The studio also plans to launch a "Talk to Columbia" mailbox on 
America Online in conjunction with the movie "Blankman," opening Aug. 19. AMY 
HARMON 
