<P>
 Landmark Bancorp: The parent company of Landmark Bank in La Habra reported 
that its profit for the second quarter nearly tripled to $422,000, or 23 cents 
a share, from $156,000, or 8 cents a share, for the same period a year earlier. 
First-half profit doubled to $607,000, or 33 cents a share, from $301,000, or 
16 cents a share. Year-to-date total assets rose 6% to $217.7 million from 
$204.8 million. 
</P>
