ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fluor Corp.: The company said Thursday that its Fluor Daniel subsidiary has 
been awarded a three-year contract for maintenance and modification services at 
the Palo Verde nuclear power plant outside Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
 Fluor Daniel was chosen by Arizona Public Service Co. for the work on the 
power plant, the largest nuclear facility in the United States. The job will 
employ as many as 150 workers, the company said. The Irvine-based Fluor Daniel 
has done maintenance and modification for 15 nuclear generating plants over the 
years. 
</P>
